  • IECF Privacy Policy

    At IECF we are committed to protecting the privacy and security of the organizations participating on our platform. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard your information. By using our platform, you consent to the practices described below.

    1.     Information We Collect

    We may collect various types of information from individuals & organizations participating on our platform, including but not limited to:

    ·       Contact information (such as name, email address, phone number)

    ·       Organization details (such as name, address, website)

    ·       User-generated content (such as comments, posts, and files shared on the platform)

    ·       Usage data (such as IP addresses, browser type, device information)

    2.     Use of Information

    We use the collected information for the following purposes:

    ·       To provide and improve our platform's services

    ·       To communicate with organizations regarding their participation on the platform

    ·       To personalize user experience and understand usage patterns

    ·       To respond to inquiries or requests from organizations

    ·       To enforce our terms of service and prevent fraudulent activities

    3.     Sharing of Information

    We may share certain information with third parties in the following circumstances:

    ·       With service providers who assist us in operating our platform and delivering services.

    ·       With affiliated companies or partners involved in providing specific features or services.

    ·       When required by law or to protect our rights or the rights of others.

    4.     Data Security

    We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect the security of your information. However, please note that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure.

    5.     Retention of Information

    We retain your information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this privacy policy unless a longer retention period is required by law.

    6.     Third-Party Links

    Our platform may contain links to third-party websites or services that are not owned or controlled by us. We are not responsible for their privacy practices and encourage you to review their privacy policies.

    7.     Children's Privacy

    Our platform is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child without parental consent, we will take steps to remove the information promptly.

    8.     Changes to this Privacy Policy

    We reserve the right to modify or update this privacy policy at any time. We will notify organizations of any material changes through a prominent notice on our platform or via email.

    9.     Contact Us

    If you have any questions or concerns regarding this privacy policy or our practices, please contact us at info@rcg-consultinggroup.com.

    By participating on our platform, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this privacy policy and agree to its terms and conditions.
